Jeff Wicks, News24(Nielen de Klerk, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban - Police are investigating a murder at a Durban beachfront hotel after the body of a man, who was shot twice in the head, was discovered on Thursday. &nbsp;It is understood that the man, covered with a blanket, was discovered in a room on the 12th floor of the Durban Spa hotel on South Beach.According to a source with knowledge of the incident, but who could not be named, the man was found in the bed of the hotel room.&ldquo;He had been covered with a blanket as if he was sleeping. On closer inspection it was noticed that the man had sustained two gunshot wounds to the head,&rdquo; the source said.&ldquo;It would appear that the man had been shot through a pillow in an effort to silence the shots. The pillow was also found at the scene."Police spokesperson, Major Thulani Zwane, as well as a spokesperson for the hotel, were unavailable for comment at the time of publishing.In another incident, a man was shot and killed by a security guard at the Mount Edgecombe railway station on Wednesday night.&ldquo;A man in his thirties was fatally shot allegedly by a security guard at a railway station after an argument,&rdquo; he said.&ldquo;He sustained three gunshot wounds. Phoenix police arrested a 48-year-old male and he will be charged for murder. He will appear in the Verulam Magistrate's Court soon,&rdquo; Zwane said.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.